    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>New York 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May &#39;85<lb/>
                144 E. 65<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd S. Morais<lb/>
                Phila<lb/>
                My dear Sr<lb/></p>
            <p>Your letter of yesterday&#39;s<lb/> date duly reached me this morning&#44; and<lb/> as its contents were interesting to our local Board<lb/> of Ministers I placed it before them during<lb/> our today&#39;s session.<lb/></p>
            <p>I regret the probable failure<lb/> of the endeavor to unify our &#94; American work for the<lb/> Alliance&#44; but we have done the next best<lb/> thing in arranging for a consolidation of<lb/> New York societies into one branch. The 19th<lb/> Congn may not immediately come into this<lb/> project&#44; but there is room for hopes&#44; that it<lb/> will eventually do so. In order to meet the<lb/> difficulties which beset the chances of Union<lb/> in this matter&#44; we have resolved on the<lb/> following plan. Each member is to seek to<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>enlist cooperation and procure members<lb/> within his own Congn&#44; then forming an<lb/> <sic>&#34;auxilliary&#34;</sic>   Asscn.  But a Central<lb/>  Body will be formed here&#44; who are to act<lb/> as intermediaries&#44; and thro whom all<lb/> Coms. are to pass&#44; and all remittances made.<lb/> As to the latter&#44; the names of donors&#44; and by whom<lb/> obtained are to be specifically mentioned&#44; thus<lb/> crediting the individual Congrs.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Central Body &#40;or Committee&#41; to be<lb/> located in this city and to act for New York  and<lb/> any other place that may voluntarily make<lb/> them the channel of Com with &#94; the Paris parent<lb/> Society&#44; will  be composed of Messr M.S. Isaacs&#44;<lb/> L T Brush&#44; William  Strauss&#44; Rev Dr H P. Mendes<lb/> severally representing 44<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.&#44; my Congn&#44; Beth El&#44; &#38; 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/> Dr Gottheil &#94;is  to select a member from Temple Emanu El.<lb/> A meeting to organize will be called for next<lb/> Monday Evening.  So now&#44; Union so far&#44; and<lb/> I trust&#44; more extended in a few months will<lb/> very probably be reached. This was the only<lb/> method of solving a somewhat difficult question.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Reciprocating your kind<lb/> regards and with assurances of esteem&#44;<lb/>
                Believe me<lb/>
                Yours truly<lb/>
                Henry S. Jacobs<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
